teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Bashley Football Club is a football club based in Bashley, near New Milton, Hampshire, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Bashley Road.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Bemerton Heath Harlequins Football Club, Bemerton Heath Harlequins FC, BHHFC
teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Bemerton Heath Harlequins Football Club is a football club based in Bemerton, Salisbury, England. Established in 1989 as a merger of Bemerton Athletic, Moon and Bemerton Boys, they are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Moon Park.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Bideford Association Football Club is a football club based in Bideford, Devon, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at the Sports Ground. The club are nicknamed "The Robins" due to their all-red strip.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Bishop's Cleeve Football Club is a semi-professional football club based in Bishop's Cleeve, near Cheltenham, Gloucestershire, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Kayte Lane. Nicknamed 'The Mitres', the club are affiliated to the Gloucestershire County FA.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Bristol Manor Farm Football Club is an English football club based in Bristol, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at The Creek. The club is affiliated to the Gloucestershire County FA.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Cinderford Town Association Football Club is a football club based in Cinderford in Gloucestershire, England. Affiliated to the Gloucestershire County FA, they are currently members of the Hellenic League Premier Division and play at the Causeway Ground.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Cribbs FC, Cribbs Football Club, Royal Sunlife Assurance
teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Cribbs Football Club is an English football club founded in 1958 and based at Cribbs Causeway, South Gloucestershire. They are currently members of Southern League Division One South and are affiliated to the Gloucestershire County FA.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN:
Didcot Town Football Club are a football club based in Didcot in Oxfordshire, England. The club is affiliated to the Berks & Bucks Football Association They won the FA Vase in 2005 and are currently members of Division One Central of the Southern League, having been relegated from the Premier Division in 2010–11.

The first team is currently managed by Jamie Heapy and his assistant manager Paul Bedwell.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Evesham United Football Club are an English football club based in Evesham, Worcestershire. They reached the First Round Proper of the FA Cup for the first time in the 2008–09 season. In 2005, they entered the Southern League Premier Division for the first time in their history but were relegated after just one season. They are affiliated to the Worcestershire County Football Association.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Exmouth Town Football Club is a football club based in Exmouth, Devon, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Southern Road.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Falmouth Town Association Football Club is a football club based in Falmouth, Cornwall, United Kingdom. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Bickland Park. The club were the first Cornish team to reach the first round proper of the FA Cup, which they have done on three occasions; 1962–63, 1967–68 and 1969–70.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Helston Athletic Football Club is a football club based in Helston, Cornwall, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Kellaway Park.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Larkhall Athletic Football Club is a football club based in the Larkhall area of Bath, Somerset, England. Affiliated to the Somerset County FA, they are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at the Plain Ham ground.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Malvern Town Football Club, MTFC, Malvern Town FC
teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Malvern Town Football Club is a football club based in Malvern, Worcestershire, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at the Langland Stadium.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Melksham Town Football Club is a football club based in Melksham, Wiltshire, England. Affiliated to the Wiltshire Football Association, they are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at the Oakfield Stadium.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Mousehole Association Football Club is a football club based in Paul, Cornwall. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Trungle Parc. It is named for the nearby village of Mousehole.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Shaftesbury Football Club are a football club based in Shaftesbury, Dorset, England. The club is affiliated to the Dorset County Football Association and is a FA chartered Standard club. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South.

teams.strTeamAlternate: Tavistock Association Football Club, Tavistock AFC
teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Tavistock Association Football Club is a football club based in Tavistock, Devon, England. They play in the Southern League Division One South.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Thatcham Town Football Club is a semi-professional English football club based in Thatcham, Berkshire. They are currently members of the Isthmian League South Central Division and play at Waterside Park. The club is affiliated to the Berks & Bucks Football Association

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Westbury United Football Club are a football club based at Meadow Lane, Westbury, Wiltshire, England. From the 2022–23 season, their first team plays in the Southern League.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Willand Rovers Football Club is a football club based in Willand, near Exeter, in Devon. They are currently members of the Southern League Division One South and play at Silver Street. The club is affiliated to the Devon County Football Association.

teams.strLeague: England Non League Div One Southern Central
teams.strDescriptionEN: Yate Town Football Club is a football club based in Yate, Gloucestershire, England. They are currently members of the Southern League Premier Division South and play at Lodge Road.
